<h1>Problem 510 - 2011 IMOSL, G4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute triangle with circumcircle \(\Omega\). Let \(B_0\) be the midpoint of \(AC\) and let \(C_0\) be the midpoint of \(AB\). Let \(D\) be the foot of the altitude from \(A\) and let \(G\) be the centroid of the triangle \(ABC\). Let \(\omega\) be a circle through \(B_0\) and \(C_0\) that is tangent to the circle \(\Omega\) at a point \(X\not= A\). Prove that the points \(D,G\) and \(X\) are collinear.</p>
